@9011  = ~Ultrablast~
@9012  = ~Ultrablast: this is a massive, omnidirectional psionic blast which savagely attacks the minds of the psion's enemies. All such enemies within 20 feet must saving throw with a -3 penalty or be stunned for three rounds. 

Using this ability costs 20 points, and increases the psion's fatigue.~
@9021  = ~Energy Construct~
@9022  = ~Energy Construct: this ability collects and concentrates energy into the shape of a fiery humanoid, which can act and even fight on the psion's behalf.

Using this ability costs 20 points, and increases the psion's fatigue.~
@9031  = ~Fission~
@9032  = ~Fission: this ability creates a fully functioning, fully cognizant clone of the psion. The clone has roughly half of the psion's experience and vitality, and operates according to the psion's will (since they are in fact the same person). Maintaining the clone's corporeal integrity involves a supreme act of will; the clone disintegrates after 1 turn.

Using this ability costs 20 points, and increases the psion's fatigue.~
@9041  = ~Atomic Disruption~
@9042  = ~Atomic Disruption: this ability manifests as a violent intrusion into the energy and form of the target, tearing apart individual cells and molecules. This roots the target to the spot and causes 10d10 damage. (The target may make a saving throw with a -2 penalty for half damage.)

Using this ability costs 20 points, and increases the psion's fatigue.~
@9051  = ~Exoskeleton~
@9052  = ~Exoskeleton: this power allows the psion to wrap <PRO_HISHER> body with layers of telekinetic force, creating a near-impenetrable shell of pure will. Visually, <PRO_HISHER> body seems to be encased in a dull, metallic sheen. 

Maintaining this ability costs 20 points; upon releasing the exoskeleton, the psion's fatigue is increased.~
@9053  = ~Cancel Exoskeleton~
@9061  = ~Elemental Composition~
@9062  = ~Elemental Composition: this power allows the psion to infuse his very body with elemental energy, taking on form of pure fire, cold, or lightning.

Maintaining this ability costs 20 points; upon returning to <PRO_HISHER> normal form, the psion's fatigue is increased.~
@9063  = ~Cancel Elemental Composition~
@9066  = ~Lightning Composition~
@9067  = ~Fire Compisition~
@9068  = ~Ice Composition~
@9071  = ~Clairvoyant Channeling~
@9072  = ~Clairvoyant Channeling: this ability allows the psion to manifest powers anywhere <PRO_HESHE> can perceive, circumventing the usual 30-foot limit. This includes areas viewable via psychic remote viewing and magical farsight, as well as any area being currently scouted by one of the psion's companions.

Maintaining this ability costs 20 points; upon ending the effect, the psion's fatigue is increased.~
@9073  = ~Cancel Clairvoyant Channeling~ 
@9081  = ~Dimensional Anchor~
@9082  = ~Dimensional Anchor: this ability creates a psychic tether between the psion's physical form and <PRO_HISHER> current plane of existence. This prevents the psion from suffering the effects of any spell of similar phenomenon that hinders <PRO_HISHER> movement in any way, or teleports or otherwise uproots <PRO_HIMHER> from that plane without consent.

Maintaining this ability costs 20 points; upon ending the effect, the psion's fatigue is increased.~
@9083  = ~Cancel Dimensional Anchor~
@9091  = ~Stasis Field~
@9092  = ~Stasis Field: this ability freezes all beings in the vicinity, at a molecular level. For twelve seconds the psion alone may move and interact with the timeless world. The stasis field prevents the psion from physically damaging anything during this time, but <PRO_HESHE> may initiate psionic abilities or magical powers, the effects of which will take place once the stasis ends. Beware: beings with near-godlike powers or characteristics may be immune to the effects of a stasis field.

Using this ability costs 20 points, and increases the psion's fatigue.~
@9101  = ~Body Control~
@9102  = ~Body Control: this ability represents the ultimate control over one's own biological processes. The psion can make <PRO_HIMHER>self completely immune to environmental damage such as acid, fire, cold, lightning, poison, or to physical damage such as crushing, slashing, or piercing/missile injuries. While the ability is maintained, the psion can change immunity at will to match whatever adverse conditions <PRO_HESHE> is currently facing.

Maintaining this ability costs 20 points; upon ending the effect, the psion's fatigue is increased.~
